columns.name: Job #
columns.description: Number assigned by DOB to Job Filing

columns.name: Borough
columns.description: 1= Manhattan, 2= Bronx, 3 = Brooklyn, 4 = Queens, 5 = Staten Island

columns.name: House #
columns.description: House Number of Residence or Commercial Property

columns.name: Street Name
columns.description: Street Name where Property is located

columns.name: Block
columns.description: Tax block assigned by Department of Finance

columns.name: Lot
columns.description: Tax lot assigned by Department of Finance

columns.name: Bin #
columns.description: Number assigned by City Planning to a specific building

columns.name: Job Type
columns.description: Job Type, based on DOB Job Code (NB-New Building, A1, A2, A3- Alterations 1-3, SG-Sign, etc.)

columns.name: Job Status
columns.description: DOB Status code of job (A-Pre Filed, I-Sign Off, P- Approved, R-Permit Entire) Complete List - http://www.nyc.gov/html/dob/downloads/pdf/bisjobstatus.pdf

columns.name: Community - Board
columns.description: 3-digit identifier: Borough code = first position, last 2 = community board

columns.name: Landmarked
columns.description: L code indicates that the building has been assigned landmark status

columns.name: eFiling Filed
columns.description: Application Filed electronically, rather than manually

columns.name: Applicant License #
columns.description: Number assigned to the skilled trade person/contractor or licensed professional

columns.name: Professional Cert
columns.description: Job is Professionally Certified by Licensed Professional instead of having it reviewed by Department of Building's Plan Examiners

columns.name: Fully Paid
columns.description: Date when job is paid and entered

columns.name: Plan Assigned Date
columns.description: Date when job is assigned to plan examiner

columns.name: Fully Permitted
columns.description: Date when job is fully permitted

columns.name: DOBRunDate
columns.description: Date when query is run and pushed to Open Data. Could be used to differentiate report dates.

view.description: Outdoor advertising regulations and zoning laws reduce visual clutter and protect people from dangerous and illegally installed signs. Signs must comply with regulations outlined in the NYC Construction Codes and the NYC Zoning Resolution. This dataset lists all sign applications filed in New York City.
view.emailShareUrl: mailto:?subject=DOB Sign Application Filings&body=Here is a dataset from NYC Open Data that I would like to share with you: https%3A%2F%2Fdata.cityofnewyork.us%2FHousing-Development%2FDOB-Sign-Application-Filings%2Fnyis-y4yr
